ching analyses range from fashion to depression to the writings of autistics, in each case affirming the neurodiversity of the minor and the alternative politics it gestures toward.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aAutism. 0aCognitive neurosciencexPhilosophy. 0aPerception (Philosophy) 0aPerception (Philosophy). 0aPolitical psychology. 0aSelf (Philosophy) 0aSelf (Philosophy). 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Deconstruction.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374411zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374411423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374411.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles